HEADWORD: Sodium sulphate
<hw>So"di*um sul"phate</hw>. <def>A salt well known as a catharic under
the name of <altname>Glauber's salt</altname>, which term is properly
applied to the hydrate, <chform>Na2SO4.10H2O</chform>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sodomite</ent>⟦br⟧
